Source:  Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  11
Edition:
Quote:  Buzzy bee, made from 1948 by Auckland company H.E. Ramsay, was copied from a toy brought from the United states, the Ramsay family confirmed yesterday... A worker at the factory in 1948 brought an American Buzzy bee toy to Mr Ramsay, and suggested something similar be made...The American Buzzy bee was flat-sided, about one and a half inches thick, made from timber with a metal clacker and covered by painted paper. That accurately describes the Fisher Price bee, which Oamaru man Gerald Lynch-Blosse bought in Arkansas about five years ago.
