Date:  0/0/1989
Source:  Dinkum Kiwi Dictionary, The
Author:  McGILL
Vol / Page:  18
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Buzzy Bee</i> although now made in China of some wood other than native tawa, this dinkum Kiwi wooden bumblebee, which has been pulled along by generations of toddlers who have delighted in its clacking wings (once wood, now plastic), was the creation of Auckland toymaker Hec Ramsay back c.1946. Once Prince William declared an interest it became a worldwide plaything.
